{
  "stem": "20089.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And now I have-- I feel almost part of them, one of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My uncle Zally, the children-- his children-- my cousin Garrick, who's at Harvard, and his sister, who's recently died, who were brought up and brought into America through Uncle Zally.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Garrick was in Stutthof with Uncle Zally, who was in Stutthof.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- Zally's children were taken out of the Kovno ghetto and put into orphanages-- three different orphanages with four-- three different children by Zally's sister-in-law, who looked non-Jewish because she was blonde and she spoke German fluently.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She took the-- she stole the children one evening and, with the help of some Lithuanian Christian children, put them into three different orphanages and only collected them after the war, when-- She survived by living as a Christian.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after the war, she collected the three children and brought them-- took them to Berlin, and then heard that Zally, who'd got out of Stutthof, was in Munich, contacted him, and told him that his children were alive, but his wife had-- had not survived the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was killed in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he went to fetch them, his two children, and the other child that-- whose parents were killed in the war.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The other child was Ellen, who's a sister of Garrick.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Garrick had joined the Hashomer and was in the camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In-- in fact, he was in-- in Rosenheim.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he left with the underground for Palestine, one of the illegal-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] one of the illegal transports through to Haifa.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Hour In fact, he didn't reach Haifa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He landed up in Cyprus, but eventually went to Haifa.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he went to university.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
